1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,405
ARCHIE: <i>Previously on</i> Riverdale...

2
00:00:01,408 --> 00:00:03,842
You only have enough in the bank to
cover three more weeks of payroll.

3
00:00:03,844 --> 00:00:05,644
I'm waiting to hear on this huge bid.

4
00:00:05,646 --> 00:00:07,813
That new development where
the old drive-in used to be?

5
00:00:07,816 --> 00:00:09,815
HERMIONE: <i>I kissed Fred Andrews.</i>

6
00:00:09,817 --> 00:00:12,297
VERONICA: The other thing. It
involves you forging my signature

7
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:15,237
to get Fred Andrews that stupid
contract to build on Dad's land.

8
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:19,268
You hated Jason, and now Polly
is pregnant with his baby.

9
00:00:19,271 --> 00:00:22,526
Of course you can stay. Anything
for Alice Cooper's daughters.

10
00:00:22,529 --> 00:00:24,929
- So where are you gonna live now?
- I'll figure it out, Dad.

11
00:00:24,932 --> 00:00:28,110
He was stealing from the company
and selling stuff on the side.

12
00:00:28,113 --> 00:00:29,867
<i>When someone is drowning,</i>

13
00:00:29,870 --> 00:00:32,830
<i>you can try to save them, but not if
they're gonna drag you down with them.</i>

14
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:37,956
[MUSIC PLAYS]

15
00:00:40,668 --> 00:00:42,279
JUGHEAD: <i>The Coopers.</i>

16
00:00:42,282 --> 00:00:45,481
<i>The Stepfords of Riverdale.</i>

17
00:00:45,484 --> 00:00:47,733
<i>High school sweethearts who got married</i>

18
00:00:47,735 --> 00:00:51,204
<i>and had two beautiful
daughters, Polly and Betty...</i>

19
00:00:53,270 --> 00:00:55,337
<i>Until Jason Blossom happened.</i>

20
00:00:56,202 --> 00:01:00,613
<i>And now, we would hear from the person
who was closest to him those days</i>

21
00:01:00,615 --> 00:01:02,515
<i>leading up to his disappearance...</i>

22
00:01:03,027 --> 00:01:04,326
<i>Polly Cooper.</i>

23
00:01:04,329 --> 00:01:09,422
<i>How a casual conversation turned
into an epic, forbidden romance.</i>

24
00:01:09,425 --> 00:01:11,528
<i>How, for reasons still murky, their</i>

25
00:01:11,531 --> 00:01:14,295
<i>respective parents tried
to tear them apart.</i>

26
00:01:14,298 --> 00:01:16,249
<i>How their break-up was short-lived,</i>

27
00:01:16,252 --> 00:01:19,999
<i>because Polly soon learned she
was pregnant with Jason's baby.</i>

28
00:01:21,921 --> 00:01:24,270
<i>How they became secretly engaged</i>

29
00:01:24,273 --> 00:01:27,593
<i>with his grandmother's
blessing and her heirloom ring,</i>

30
00:01:29,213 --> 00:01:31,313
<i>and made plans to run away together,</i>

31
00:01:32,614 --> 00:01:34,013
<i>to start a new life.</i>

32
00:01:34,016 --> 00:01:38,451
<i>And how their dreams of
escape went up in flames.</i>

33
00:01:41,646 --> 00:01:43,146
That was the last day you saw him?

34
00:01:43,149 --> 00:01:45,349
At Pop's, when he told me the plan,

35
00:01:45,352 --> 00:01:46,955
that he was gonna fake his own death,

36
00:01:46,958 --> 00:01:48,186
and then we would meet up.

37
00:01:48,189 --> 00:01:52,444
But, before that could happen,
my mom and dad sent me away.

38
00:01:52,447 --> 00:01:55,780
One of Jason's teammates
said that before he ran away,

39
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:57,282
Jason was dealing drugs.

40
00:01:57,285 --> 00:01:59,872
Making a one-time delivery.

41
00:01:59,875 --> 00:02:02,884
He needed... We needed money.

42
00:02:02,887 --> 00:02:04,665
To get away and to start over.

43
00:02:04,668 --> 00:02:08,138
So Riverdale's star football
player becomes a drug mule?

44
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:09,939
He went to a bar on the
other side of the tracks

45
00:02:09,941 --> 00:02:12,608
and made a deal with some biker gang.

46
00:02:12,611 --> 00:02:13,777
The Serpents?

47
00:02:13,779 --> 00:02:16,179
He got an address upstate,

48
00:02:16,182 --> 00:02:19,175
where he was supposed to deliver
the drugs in exchange for cash.

49
00:02:19,178 --> 00:02:21,222
The drugs you found in Jason's car...

50
00:02:22,316 --> 00:02:23,815
- Yeah.
- ...that went up in flames.

51
00:02:23,818 --> 00:02:26,623
Along with everything
I had left of Jason,

52
00:02:26,626 --> 00:02:28,832
including the ring his nana gave me,

53
00:02:28,835 --> 00:02:31,561
which he was keeping until...

54
00:02:32,931 --> 00:02:35,665
Okay, Sheriff, I think
that's enough for tonight.

55
00:02:35,668 --> 00:02:37,567
I think Polly needs her rest.

56
00:02:37,570 --> 00:02:39,702
I'll be in touch, ladies.

57
00:02:39,705 --> 00:02:42,105
- I'll show you out.
- Thank you.

58
00:02:45,082 --> 00:02:46,721
We're gonna get you through this, okay?

59
00:02:53,561 --> 00:02:56,019
[MAN SCREAMING AND GROANING]

60
00:02:56,022 --> 00:02:59,094
- JUGHEAD: Gotta stop blowing me up.
- You're going the wrong way.

61
00:02:59,097 --> 00:03:01,758
- You're going the... What are you doing?
- [GUNSHOTS IN GAME]

62
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:03,026
Come on.

63
00:03:03,029 --> 00:03:05,566
You're the one who keeps
accidentally killing me.

64
00:03:05,569 --> 00:03:06,963
War is hell, Jug.

65
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:10,333
No, Archie, hell is other people.

66
00:03:10,336 --> 00:03:12,969
- [KNOCKS]
- Hey, guys, getting pretty late...

67
00:03:12,971 --> 00:03:14,904
And... Whoa! It's kinda ripe in here.

68
00:03:14,906 --> 00:03:16,072
Does someone wanna open a window?

69
00:03:16,074 --> 00:03:17,273
I got it.

70
00:03:18,376 --> 00:03:20,810
- You settling in, Jug?
- JUGHEAD: Oh, completely.

71
00:03:20,813 --> 00:03:23,780
It's like Archie and I are just
roommates in a college dorm.

72
00:03:23,782 --> 00:03:25,849
Oh, great. What does
that make me, the RA?

73
00:03:25,852 --> 00:03:27,718
No, you're the third roommate.

74
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,587
All right, guys. I
got a big day tomorrow.

75
00:03:30,589 --> 00:03:32,589
Yeah, breaking ground on
the SoDale project, right?

76
00:03:32,592 --> 00:03:34,157
Yeah. Indeed, we are.

77
00:03:35,288 --> 00:03:37,893
Sorry, 'cause I know it's kind
of a sore spot with you, Jughead,

78
00:03:37,896 --> 00:03:39,062
about the drive-in.

79
00:03:39,065 --> 00:03:41,794
As long as you build something
beautiful in its place.

80
00:03:41,797 --> 00:03:45,415
Well, I don't know about
beautiful, but it's gonna be big.

81
00:03:45,418 --> 00:03:47,704
- Night, guys.
- Night, Dad.

82
00:03:54,012 --> 00:03:56,045
<i>♪ Talking television at the... ♪</i>

83
00:03:56,047 --> 00:03:58,982
Polly's convinced herself
that no one wants her baby.

84
00:03:58,984 --> 00:04:01,972
Besides, of course, the
child-snatching Blossom monsters.

85
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:05,088
- No offense, Cheryl.
- None taken.

86
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:07,223
So your mom and dad want
Polly but not the baby,

87
00:04:07,225 --> 00:04:09,626
and the Blossoms want
the baby and not Polly.

88
00:04:09,629 --> 00:04:12,462
That's a true Gordian knot.

89
00:04:12,465 --> 00:04:15,220
It's an impossible situation.

90
00:04:15,223 --> 00:04:16,833
Betty, come on.

91
00:04:16,835 --> 00:04:18,935
An impossible situation is being invited

92
00:04:18,937 --> 00:04:20,859
to both the <i>Vanity Flair</i> Oscar party

93
00:04:20,862 --> 00:04:23,273
and Elton John's Oscar
party on the same night.

94
00:04:23,275 --> 00:04:25,375
Which happened to me one year, I know.

95
00:04:25,378 --> 00:04:27,911
This is merely an annoying situation.

96
00:04:27,914 --> 00:04:31,981
But luckily, I've been
percolating on an idea,

97
00:04:31,984 --> 00:04:34,250
hellishly simple in its conception.

98
00:04:34,253 --> 00:04:37,620
What if my mom and I were
to host a baby shower?

99
00:04:37,623 --> 00:04:38,542
Count me in.

100
00:04:38,545 --> 00:04:41,691
You want Polly to feel
loved and supported, right?

101
00:04:41,694 --> 00:04:44,661
Yeah, but ideally by her own parents.

102
00:04:44,663 --> 00:04:46,996
Okay, so, baby steps, girl.

103
00:04:46,999 --> 00:04:49,666
Get Polly and your
parents in the same room

104
00:04:49,669 --> 00:04:51,668
in a public setting
where they can't fight,

105
00:04:51,670 --> 00:04:54,037
and, <i>voila,</i> let the healing begin.

106
00:04:54,039 --> 00:04:55,571
Am I expected to come to this thing?

107
00:04:55,573 --> 00:04:56,485
Of course!

108
00:04:56,488 --> 00:04:58,882
You're Betty's boyfriend, so...

109
00:04:59,404 --> 00:05:01,404
Oh, my God, you guys, relax.

110
00:05:01,407 --> 00:05:04,534
It's just a word that
starts with the letter "B."

111
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:07,072
Betty, what do you say?

112
00:05:08,553 --> 00:05:09,819
Elizabeth Cooper.

113
00:05:09,822 --> 00:05:10,933
Mom?

114
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:12,855
I need you and you.

115
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:15,429
Right now.

116
00:05:19,597 --> 00:05:22,932
Hey, Vic, I was just getting ready to
come out and walk you through the day.

117
00:05:24,869 --> 00:05:28,538
Hate to do this to you, Fred,
but, um... I gotta pull my crew.

118
00:05:30,216 --> 00:05:32,408
Before we've even
started? What happened?

119
00:05:32,411 --> 00:05:34,018
Cliff Blossom reached out.

120
00:05:34,021 --> 00:05:35,878
Says he's got a big job coming up.

121
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,320
Says he needs us free and available.

122
00:05:37,323 --> 00:05:38,549
[SIGHS]

123
00:05:38,552 --> 00:05:41,584
Blossom's willing to guarantee
us two years' work, starting now.

124
00:05:41,587 --> 00:05:43,753
Can't ask my guys to turn
down that kind of money.

125
00:05:43,755 --> 00:05:45,188
No, Vic, I can't.

126
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:46,522
Sorry, Fred.

127
00:05:51,484 --> 00:05:54,297
Sheriff Keller told us everything.

128
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:56,382
How you're hiding
Polly at the Pembrooke?

129
00:05:56,385 --> 00:05:58,701
Better than in an insane asylum.

130
00:05:58,703 --> 00:06:00,773
VERONICA: Actually, Mrs.
Cooper, that's on me.

131
00:06:00,776 --> 00:06:03,372
I was the one who suggested
that Polly stay with us.

132
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:05,028
She's trying to help.

133
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:08,317
Unlike you and Dad, who want Polly
to give the baby up for adoption.

134
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:10,708
Betty, it's what's best
for Polly and the baby.

135
00:06:10,711 --> 00:06:13,216
Mom, that's not your choice.

136
00:06:13,219 --> 00:06:17,299
Your choice is whether or not you
want to be a part of Polly's life.

137
00:06:19,301 --> 00:06:22,169
Veronica and her mom have
offered to host a baby shower.

138
00:06:22,172 --> 00:06:24,281
Well, that is hardly appropriate!

139
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:25,528
Really?

140
00:06:26,464 --> 00:06:28,898
Because I think it's an amazing idea.

141
00:06:29,987 --> 00:06:33,136
You want to be loving and
supportive like a normal grandmother?

142
00:06:33,138 --> 00:06:34,604
Then, great.

143
00:06:34,606 --> 00:06:37,362
Otherwise, stay away.

144
00:06:42,772 --> 00:06:45,925
Don, I just need a few
guys from your crew.

145
00:06:45,928 --> 00:06:48,618
FRED: A couple to get me started.

146
00:06:48,621 --> 00:06:52,229
I did check. I'll get back to you, Don.

147
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:56,426
What was that about?

148
00:06:56,961 --> 00:06:58,327
It's all good.

149
00:06:58,330 --> 00:07:00,196
How was your date with Val?

150
00:07:00,198 --> 00:07:02,732
It was good. I got you some slices.

151
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:07,970
Did something happen at work?

152
00:07:07,973 --> 00:07:13,910
Cliff Blossom made my crew an offer
they couldn't refuse so they walked.

153
00:07:13,913 --> 00:07:15,978
Every last one of 'em.

154
00:07:15,981 --> 00:07:17,769
Screw em, then.

155
00:07:17,772 --> 00:07:20,836
Anyone who'd rather work for Clifford
Blossom than you is crazy, Dad.

156
00:07:24,596 --> 00:07:26,388
Dad?

157
00:07:26,391 --> 00:07:27,657
What is it?

158
00:07:28,047 --> 00:07:30,693
You always make me talk
to you about my problems.

159
00:07:33,605 --> 00:07:37,068
The business... It's in trouble, Archie.

160
00:07:37,071 --> 00:07:38,935
Has been for a long time.

161
00:07:38,938 --> 00:07:41,671
Big jobs are just few and far between.

162
00:07:41,674 --> 00:07:44,740
That's why this SoDale
thing is so important to me.

163
00:07:45,817 --> 00:07:47,510
I can't break ground without a crew,

164
00:07:47,512 --> 00:07:50,279
so every day I'm just hemorrhaging cash.

165
00:07:50,281 --> 00:07:54,150
We've got equipment sitting there,
supplies, bills that are past due.

166
00:07:54,152 --> 00:07:57,186
[STAMMERING] Dad, why didn't
you tell me? I had no idea.

167
00:07:57,189 --> 00:08:00,156
[SIGHS] It was never
supposed to get this bad.

168
00:08:01,292 --> 00:08:03,126
You work your ass off
to build something,

169
00:08:03,128 --> 00:08:06,028
and in one false step
you could lose everything.

170
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,930
No, Dad, you're not losing anything.

171
00:08:09,334 --> 00:08:10,700
We'll figure this out.

172
