173
00:08:21,159 --> 00:08:23,737
A Baby Shower? You should that's
a good idea. You know, when...

174
00:08:23,739 --> 00:08:25,138
- It is.
- It's a great idea.

175
00:08:25,141 --> 00:08:26,594
What about Mom and Dad?

176
00:08:26,597 --> 00:08:29,510
What do you want, honey?
Do you want them to come?

177
00:08:29,512 --> 00:08:31,678
I do. I mean, Mom, at least.

178
00:08:31,681 --> 00:08:34,481
In that case, we'll
get her there somehow.

179
00:08:34,483 --> 00:08:36,183
But I do not want to fight with her.

180
00:08:36,185 --> 00:08:37,417
BETTY: You won't.

181
00:08:37,419 --> 00:08:40,347
The entire Cooper family will
support you on this, Polly.

182
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:42,250
I want the Blossoms there.

183
00:08:42,253 --> 00:08:44,590
- Cheryl, sure, yeah, she's on the guest list.
- Cheryl.

184
00:08:44,593 --> 00:08:46,026
And Mrs. Blossom.

185
00:08:46,028 --> 00:08:48,862
She just tried to declare
you an unfit mother.

186
00:08:48,864 --> 00:08:51,698
Well, then this shower
is the perfect opportunity

187
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,467
for me to prove to her that I'm not.

188
00:08:54,803 --> 00:08:57,037
- Ronnie? A word?
- Hmm?

189
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,572
Sure.

190
00:08:58,575 --> 00:09:00,307
Excuse us.

191
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:10,651
The Blossoms and the Coopers
in our pre-war apartment?

192
00:09:10,653 --> 00:09:11,985
It'll be a bloodbath!

193
00:09:11,988 --> 00:09:13,754
They've been the
Hatfields and the McCoys

194
00:09:13,756 --> 00:09:15,856
since long before Polly was pregnant.

195
00:09:15,858 --> 00:09:18,358
Plus, I'm trying to avoid the Blossoms.

196
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,960
If they find out your father is the one

197
00:09:19,962 --> 00:09:21,461
who bought the drive-in,

198
00:09:21,463 --> 00:09:22,729
it'll be open war.

199
00:09:22,731 --> 00:09:23,830
Against us?

200
00:09:23,832 --> 00:09:25,432
They're making a play for the land,

201
00:09:25,434 --> 00:09:27,234
hoping to stop construction.

202
00:09:27,237 --> 00:09:29,701
Fred and I are trying to
keep it on track, but...

203
00:09:29,704 --> 00:09:32,272
But Mr. Andrews still doesn't
know that Daddy is the buyer?

204
00:09:32,274 --> 00:09:35,475
All of which is to say the
timing of this shower is just...

205
00:09:35,478 --> 00:09:37,144
It's not ideal.

206
00:09:37,147 --> 00:09:39,546
Plus, I can't believe
Alice even wants to come,

207
00:09:39,548 --> 00:09:40,614
from what you've told me.

208
00:09:40,616 --> 00:09:41,457
She doesn't.

209
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:44,718
I was kind of hoping you
might talk some sense into her?

210
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,720
You know, like, mother-to-mother?

211
00:09:46,722 --> 00:09:48,221
Oh, yeah, no.

212
00:09:48,223 --> 00:09:50,712
Please, Mom, she really needs our help.

213
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,873
[TIRES SCREECHING]

214
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,228
Fred.

215
00:10:05,231 --> 00:10:08,749
You try to hire my crew on
the first day of construction?

216
00:10:08,752 --> 00:10:10,514
Opportunity knocks when it knocks.

217
00:10:10,517 --> 00:10:11,645
Nothing personal.

218
00:10:11,647 --> 00:10:12,846
Yeah, it never is with you guys.

219
00:10:12,848 --> 00:10:14,598
So what is it? The development? What?

220
00:10:14,601 --> 00:10:16,968
That land you're building
on, it belonged to my family.

221
00:10:16,971 --> 00:10:19,753
We founded our maple empire on it.

222
00:10:19,756 --> 00:10:21,955
Now, we were in the process
of trying to reacquire it,

223
00:10:21,957 --> 00:10:23,323
buy it back,

224
00:10:23,325 --> 00:10:24,725
when your mysterious boss,

225
00:10:24,727 --> 00:10:27,828
he, he just stole it right
out from underneath us.

226
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:29,863
And you can't go after
him, so you come after me.

227
00:10:29,865 --> 00:10:33,931
The way your boss does
business deals, secret deals,

228
00:10:33,934 --> 00:10:36,603
building that SoDale monstrosity

229
00:10:36,605 --> 00:10:38,138
at the speed of light

230
00:10:38,141 --> 00:10:41,675
kinda makes me think that he
has a limited amount of funds.

231
00:10:41,677 --> 00:10:43,944
So you're gonna halt construction,

232
00:10:43,946 --> 00:10:45,178
bleed him out.

233
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:47,819
Reacquire the land at
a more reasonable rate.

234
00:10:47,822 --> 00:10:50,283
- That's a great plan.
- Thank you.

235
00:10:50,285 --> 00:10:53,086
Except you're bleeding me
out, too, you pompous ass.

236
00:10:54,349 --> 00:10:56,249
You're messing with my business,

237
00:10:56,252 --> 00:11:00,093
my livelihood, my son's future.

238
00:11:00,096 --> 00:11:03,063
I don't care if you're the
richest man in Riverdale.

239
00:11:03,065 --> 00:11:05,599
I will come after you
with everything I've got.

240
00:11:05,602 --> 00:11:07,300
Which is what, exactly?

241
00:11:10,735 --> 00:11:12,235
Go park somewhere else.

242
00:11:20,249 --> 00:11:21,448
[DOOR SLAMS]

243
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:22,816
How did it go with Clifford?

244
00:11:22,818 --> 00:11:25,452
Good, insofar as I didn't
knock him on his ass,

245
00:11:25,454 --> 00:11:27,587
which I would really love to do.

246
00:11:29,843 --> 00:11:32,459
He's in some kind of grudge
match with the owner of this land.

247
00:11:32,461 --> 00:11:34,127
Lucky us, we're caught in the crossfire.

248
00:11:36,532 --> 00:11:39,833
And this mysterious buyer...

249
00:11:39,835 --> 00:11:41,735
Does Cliff know who he is?

250
00:11:41,738 --> 00:11:44,106
No, he's as in the dark as we are.

251
00:11:44,109 --> 00:11:45,439
[CAR TIRES SQUEALING]

252
00:11:46,471 --> 00:11:48,174
What the hell now?

253
00:11:48,177 --> 00:11:49,476
[CAR DOORS SLAMMING]

254
00:11:56,618 --> 00:11:58,018
What is this?

255
00:11:58,020 --> 00:12:01,054
Your new crew, reporting for duty.

256
00:12:01,056 --> 00:12:04,324
I appreciate it, I do, but isn't
there something more important

257
00:12:04,326 --> 00:12:05,559
you need to be doing?

258
00:12:05,561 --> 00:12:07,379
Like going to school, playing football?

259
00:12:07,382 --> 00:12:09,496
We can work after
practice and on weekends.

260
00:12:09,498 --> 00:12:12,065
Until you find a new crew.
Help keep things on schedule.

261
00:12:12,925 --> 00:12:15,500
Come on, Dad. I worked
for you the whole summer.

262
00:12:15,503 --> 00:12:18,538
- And these guys...
- We're bruiser studs, Mr. Andrews.

263
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:19,606
At least some of us are.

264
00:12:20,943 --> 00:12:22,943
Come on. Desperate times, Fred, huh?

265
00:12:24,613 --> 00:12:25,779
[SIGHS]

266
00:12:26,512 --> 00:12:28,013
All right. Here we go.

267
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:32,219
<i>♪ Life gives me one more chance ♪</i>

268
00:12:32,222 --> 00:12:35,088
ALICE: You must be
loving this, Hermione.

269
00:12:35,091 --> 00:12:37,557
Providing sanctuary to my daughter.

270
00:12:38,694 --> 00:12:41,328
Asking me here, to what? Gloat?

271
00:12:43,098 --> 00:12:45,632
Look, I asked you here
because I'm trying to help.

272
00:12:45,635 --> 00:12:47,868
So what is your plan for Polly?

273
00:12:47,871 --> 00:12:49,936
What do you want?

274
00:12:49,939 --> 00:12:51,872
I want my daughter back.

275
00:12:52,641 --> 00:12:54,474
I want my family back together.

276
00:12:55,284 --> 00:12:57,351
Well, then, it's time to face facts.

277
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:00,747
Hermione, Polly is a teenager.

278
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:03,517
She hasn't even finished high school.

279
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:06,319
The father of her
baby has been murdered.

280
00:13:06,322 --> 00:13:10,031
You want to play house with her,
and throw her a baby shower, fine.

281
00:13:10,034 --> 00:13:13,493
But the very next day, all of
those things will still be true.

282
00:13:13,496 --> 00:13:15,734
And she's supposed to what?

283
00:13:15,737 --> 00:13:17,664
Raise a child?

284
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:19,699
Mothers do it every day.

285
00:13:20,335 --> 00:13:21,868
We did it.

286
00:13:23,238 --> 00:13:24,905
Come to the shower.

287
00:13:24,907 --> 00:13:27,073
Be there for Polly. Help her.

288
00:13:28,944 --> 00:13:31,745
Otherwise, you're gonna regret
it for the rest of your life.

289
00:13:37,245 --> 00:13:38,478
This is awesome.

290
00:13:38,481 --> 00:13:40,821
Moving rocks beats working
out in our crappy weight room.

291
00:13:40,823 --> 00:13:41,988
Hey, Keller!

292
00:13:41,991 --> 00:13:44,257
Looking good, looking buff.

293
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:46,093
We should get you on the team.

294
00:13:46,096 --> 00:13:49,362
I prefer my contact sports
one-on-one, you know, like...

295
00:13:49,364 --> 00:13:50,864
Boxing.

296
00:13:55,137 --> 00:13:57,103
Pretty handy with that
wheelbarrow, Archie.

297
00:13:57,106 --> 00:13:59,239
You know, if the whole
music thing doesn't pan out,

298
00:13:59,241 --> 00:14:01,842
you can always have
manual labor as a fallback.

299
00:14:01,844 --> 00:14:04,411
Don't even joke. I did this
all summer long, remember?

300
00:14:04,414 --> 00:14:06,179
My dad loves this kind of work.

301
00:14:06,181 --> 00:14:07,747
And I love him, but...

302
00:14:07,749 --> 00:14:08,915
No, I know.

303
00:14:08,917 --> 00:14:10,584
Your dad's path is not for you.

304
00:14:10,587 --> 00:14:12,120
Trust me, I get it.

305
00:14:12,823 --> 00:14:14,988
He works his ass off for me, bro,

306
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:16,256
but never asks for anything.

307
00:14:16,258 --> 00:14:18,491
Always has my back, even when I mess up.

308
00:14:18,494 --> 00:14:22,095
So if having his back means I gotta
haul some rocks, then bring it on.

309
00:14:22,097 --> 00:14:22,992
Agreed.

310
00:14:22,995 --> 00:14:24,961
Your dad's got my back, too.

311
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:26,477
More than some people.

312
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,779
Exactly.

313
00:14:31,473 --> 00:14:33,273
Hey, guys, you were a life-saver today.

314
00:14:33,275 --> 00:14:35,141
I appreciate it. Hard
hats go in the bin,

315
00:14:35,143 --> 00:14:36,776
and there's sodas in the fridge.

316
00:14:37,613 --> 00:14:39,312
Crap! Hey, guys, I forgot my phone.

317
00:14:47,689 --> 00:14:48,922
[BANGS]

318
00:14:49,491 --> 00:14:50,957
- [SPARKS HISSING]
- Hey!

319
00:14:52,261 --> 00:14:53,793
Hey, get away from there!

320
00:14:56,131 --> 00:14:57,764
[BANGING]

321
00:15:06,105 --> 00:15:07,274
[MOOSE GRUNTING]

322
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:16,983
- Moose, are you okay?
- [GROANS]

323
00:15:16,986 --> 00:15:18,618
Stay down. We'll get you some help.

324
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,787
- Who did this to you, Moose?
- No clue.

325
00:15:21,376 --> 00:15:23,790
But they said, as long
as we keep working,

326
00:15:23,792 --> 00:15:25,692
they're gonna keep coming back.

327
00:15:44,335 --> 00:15:45,734
What the hell happened?

328
00:15:46,614 --> 00:15:48,668
Moose, over there, he
caught a couple of

329
00:15:48,671 --> 00:15:50,973
guys working over my
equipment with a crowbar

330
00:15:50,976 --> 00:15:52,564
and then they got the drop on him.

331
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,158
Who were they, vandals?

332
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:56,139
Cliff Blossom has made
it abundantly clear

333
00:15:56,141 --> 00:15:57,173
he would love nothing more

334
00:15:57,175 --> 00:15:58,775
than to see this whole
project go belly-up.

335
00:15:58,777 --> 00:16:00,977
I doubt that Blossom's
gonna hire some thugs

336
00:16:00,979 --> 00:16:03,479
to bust up your site and
beat up some teenagers.

337
00:16:04,177 --> 00:16:05,644
Maybe it wasn't him.

338
00:16:05,647 --> 00:16:08,384
I mean, this is Serpent
territory, right?

339
00:16:08,386 --> 00:16:11,587
Maybe it was them. Pissed that they
had to leave 'cause of this project.

340
00:16:11,589 --> 00:16:13,122
- Serpents?
- Yeah.

341
00:16:13,124 --> 00:16:16,059
When I worked at the drive-in,
the Serpents never bugged me.

342
00:16:18,223 --> 00:16:20,590
Did you see any snake tattoos,
anything on their jackets?

343
00:16:20,593 --> 00:16:22,126
It happened pretty fast.

344
00:16:22,129 --> 00:16:24,701
SHERIFF KELLER: All right,
I'll talk to Blossom, but I mean

345
00:16:24,703 --> 00:16:27,103
I don't think we'll get anywhere
unless we can ID these guys.

346
00:16:27,106 --> 00:16:28,472
That is such bull.

347
00:16:28,475 --> 00:16:30,974
If this was Clifford Blossom
asking for help, you would say yes.

348
00:16:30,976 --> 00:16:32,700
- FRED: Archie.
- What, Dad? It's true.

349
00:16:32,703 --> 00:16:34,036
It's also not helping.

350
00:16:39,319 --> 00:16:41,853
Have you heard from Mom? Is she coming?

351
00:16:43,922 --> 00:16:46,055
She's invited.

352
00:16:48,531 --> 00:16:50,078
Hey, it doesn't matter.

353
00:16:50,664 --> 00:16:53,966
If Mom doesn't want to come,
that's on her. It's her loss.

354
00:16:53,969 --> 00:16:58,334
Betty, I've decided... I want
you to be the baby's godmother.

355
00:16:58,336 --> 00:17:00,615
Really? Me?

356
00:17:00,618 --> 00:17:01,683
Oh, my God!

357
00:17:01,686 --> 00:17:03,539
POLLY: If anything
would ever happen to me,

358
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:06,275
the only person I'd trust to
take care of my baby is you.

359
00:17:07,569 --> 00:17:09,636
Oh, my God, Pol!

360
00:17:14,981 --> 00:17:17,014
It's so wrong, Val!

361
00:17:17,017 --> 00:17:18,554
Things should not be this way.

362
00:17:18,556 --> 00:17:21,024
It sucks, but, please,
Archie, talk to me.

363
00:17:21,034 --> 00:17:24,039
I can't keep talking about
it, I have to do something.

364
00:17:24,042 --> 00:17:26,216
Hopefully not something you'll regret.

365
00:17:26,831 --> 00:17:27,997
[SIGHS]

366
00:17:28,414 --> 00:17:30,500
I'm sorry, Val, I have
to go, I have to try.

367
00:17:32,484 --> 00:17:34,551
VERONICA: <i>Poor Moose. Is he okay?</i>

368
00:17:34,554 --> 00:17:37,487
His name is Moose. He's fine.

369
00:17:37,489 --> 00:17:38,588
[CHUCKLES]

370
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:41,391
Dude, what the hell?
I've been texting you.

371
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:44,060
Archie, Jughead just told
us what happened yesterday.

372
00:17:44,062 --> 00:17:47,030
Though I checked out at the
words "construction" and "site."

373
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:50,019
Moose and I are going to the Southside
to find those Serpents. You in?

374
00:17:50,022 --> 00:17:53,402
Whoa! Hey, you didn't say it was
the Serpents who beat Moose up.

375
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,138
'Cause we don't know that for a fact.

376
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:57,540
Well, it's still worth a
shot if it might help my dad.

377
00:17:57,917 --> 00:17:59,775
Kevin's boyfriend can get us in.

378
00:17:59,778 --> 00:18:00,844
Get you in where?

379
00:18:00,847 --> 00:18:03,280
To some bar where the Serpents hang out.

380
00:18:03,283 --> 00:18:06,116
If Moose spots them,
we call Sheriff Keller

381
00:18:06,118 --> 00:18:07,450
and get these goons arrested.

382
00:18:07,452 --> 00:18:10,954
Archie, the Serpents are dangerous.

383
00:18:10,956 --> 00:18:12,522
They're drug-dealers.

384
00:18:12,524 --> 00:18:13,590
What?

385
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:15,506
Says who?

386
00:18:15,509 --> 00:18:17,127
Polly.

387
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:20,563
Remember? Trev told us that
Jason was dealing drugs?

388
00:18:20,565 --> 00:18:21,998
It was for the Serpents.

389
00:18:22,001 --> 00:18:24,334
You heard my Dad, Jughead.

390
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:26,403
Clifford Blossom is
trying to torpedo him.

391
00:18:26,406 --> 00:18:29,239
Sheriff Keller basically blew
him off, right in front of us.

392
00:18:29,241 --> 00:18:31,608
Somebody needs to do something.

393
00:18:32,907 --> 00:18:35,769
Archie, going into
that bar is a bad idea.

394
00:18:35,772 --> 00:18:38,648
Jughead, are you coming with me or not?

395
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,654
Thanks for having my back.

396
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:53,430
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINES REVVING]

397
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:59,536
Play it cool, just like we said.

398
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:01,428
Keep eye-contact to a minimum.

399
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:04,040
And Moose, if you see the
guys that jumped you, we leave,

400
00:19:04,042 --> 00:19:05,709
and we call Kevin's dad.

401
00:19:10,515 --> 00:19:12,215
[MUSIC PLAYING]

402
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:22,792
Moose? Anything?

403
00:19:22,794 --> 00:19:24,461
Not yet, not that I see.

404
00:19:24,463 --> 00:19:26,029
We're all gonna die.

405
00:19:30,561 --> 00:19:31,960
Pay up.

406
00:19:31,963 --> 00:19:33,803
[SIGHS] I'm gonna get this back, right?

407
00:19:33,805 --> 00:19:35,438
You wish, Preppy.

408
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:41,845
Is that one of them?

409
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,279
I can't tell.

410
00:19:43,282 --> 00:19:44,889
He looks kind of familiar.

411
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,685
Oh, God!

412
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:49,886
Hey.

413
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:54,457
What? You got a death wish?

414
00:19:54,459 --> 00:19:55,625
Archie, back off.

415
00:19:55,627 --> 00:19:56,693
What the hell is this?

416
00:19:56,695 --> 00:19:58,384
You like beating up teenagers?

417
00:19:58,387 --> 00:20:01,097
This isn't the first time one
of you Bulldogs has come in here,

418
00:20:01,099 --> 00:20:02,565
looking to 'cause trouble.

419
00:20:06,157 --> 00:20:09,372
FP: Hey! That's enough,
Mustang. Let 'em go.

420
00:20:16,209 --> 00:20:18,176
I'll take care of this.

421
00:20:32,044 --> 00:20:34,745
Not you, Red, you stay.

422
00:20:36,317 --> 00:20:37,583
I'm good.

423
00:20:42,022 --> 00:20:43,422
What the hell are you doing here?

424
00:20:43,424 --> 00:20:45,940
Looking for the thugs that
trashed my dad's equipment.

425
00:20:45,943 --> 00:20:49,228
We figured it was the Serpents, angry
for getting kicked off their land,

426
00:20:49,231 --> 00:20:51,015
but now that I know you're a Serpent,

427
00:20:51,018 --> 00:20:52,584
I'm thinking this is personal.

428
00:20:52,587 --> 00:20:54,699
Going after my dad, his company,

429
00:20:54,702 --> 00:20:56,535
that is payback, right?
For when he fired you?

430
00:20:56,537 --> 00:20:58,871
Man, you've got a bigger
imagination than Jughead,

431
00:20:58,873 --> 00:21:00,072
and that's saying something.

432
00:21:00,074 --> 00:21:01,940
This isn't a joke. My
dad could lose everything.

433
00:21:01,942 --> 00:21:03,709
You think I'm responsible?

434
00:21:03,711 --> 00:21:05,333
That I've been, what,
waiting all these years

435
00:21:05,335 --> 00:21:06,958
for a chance to get
back at your old man?

436
00:21:06,961 --> 00:21:09,898
No. No, kid, life's too short.

437
00:21:10,961 --> 00:21:13,428
You don't know that now, but you will.

438
00:21:14,352 --> 00:21:15,618
[TIRES SCREECHING]

439
00:21:17,434 --> 00:21:20,723
I called him the second
you set foot in the bar.

440
00:21:23,069 --> 00:21:24,869
Get in the truck, Archie.

441
00:21:26,476 --> 00:21:28,576
<i>♪ Our house, our house ♪</i>

442
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:30,145
<i>♪ Our house ♪</i>

443
00:21:30,147 --> 00:21:32,013
<i>♪ Our house ♪</i>

444
00:21:32,683 --> 00:21:34,949
<i>♪ In the middle of our street ♪</i>

445
00:21:34,951 --> 00:21:36,751
Hi, guys. Good to see
you. Right this way.

446
00:21:38,689 --> 00:21:41,222
- Hey. Hey.
- Good to see you.

447
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:45,794
<i>♪ Our house, it has a crowd ♪</i>

448
00:21:46,997 --> 00:21:49,531
<i>♪ There's always something happening ♪</i>

449
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,399
You're sweet to be here.

450
00:21:51,402 --> 00:21:54,002
I know this isn't exactly your scene.

451
00:21:54,004 --> 00:21:56,671
What? Organizing a baby shower?

452
00:21:57,407 --> 00:21:58,973
It's totally on my bucket list.

453
00:22:00,577 --> 00:22:01,743
Mom!

454
00:22:02,579 --> 00:22:04,846
<i>♪ Our house ♪</i>

455
00:22:05,515 --> 00:22:07,682
<i>♪ In the middle of our street ♪</i>

456
00:22:07,685 --> 00:22:08,718
<i>♪ Our house ♪</i>

457
00:22:08,721 --> 00:22:10,952
Polly, look, Mom's here!

458
00:22:18,169 --> 00:22:20,673
I'm so glad you're
here, and you're safe.

459
00:22:23,763 --> 00:22:25,162
You and the baby.

460
00:22:26,239 --> 00:22:27,405
Oh, Mom.

461
00:22:29,795 --> 00:22:32,107
We're here!

462
00:22:35,312 --> 00:22:38,313
No big deal, it's only the
best stroller money can buy.

463
00:22:38,316 --> 00:22:40,114
So expensive.

464
00:22:40,117 --> 00:22:43,518
All I ask in return is that you
make me your baby's godmother.

465
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:44,786
[BETTY CLEARS THROAT]

466
00:22:44,788 --> 00:22:46,221
- Kidding!
- [BOTH CHUCKLING]

467
00:22:46,224 --> 00:22:47,455
So not kidding.

468
00:22:49,025 --> 00:22:51,593
Come on, Nana Rose, let's get
you a good spot by the food.

469
00:22:53,730 --> 00:22:54,996
Polly.

470
00:22:55,799 --> 00:22:57,766
Let me begin with an apology.

471
00:22:57,769 --> 00:23:00,969
When I first heard about the
baby, my initial instinct,

472
00:23:00,971 --> 00:23:05,273
to embrace the baby
but not you was wrong.

473
00:23:06,943 --> 00:23:08,510
I hope you can forgive me.

474
00:23:08,513 --> 00:23:11,346
Think happy thoughts.

475
00:23:17,212 --> 00:23:19,187
So what, you're a Serpent now?

476
00:23:19,190 --> 00:23:20,983
Thought you left that behind.

477
00:23:20,986 --> 00:23:22,618
A guy's got to make a living.

478
00:23:22,621 --> 00:23:25,070
- And not many people would hire me, after...
- Right.

479
00:23:25,073 --> 00:23:26,686
It's my fault you run with criminals

480
00:23:26,689 --> 00:23:28,630
that rough up teenagers
and trash my equipment?

481
00:23:28,632 --> 00:23:30,498
You really think I'd come after you?

482
00:23:30,501 --> 00:23:34,085
That I'd put you and your kid in danger
after everything you've done for my boy?

483
00:23:35,312 --> 00:23:36,744
Look, I'm

484
00:23:37,941 --> 00:23:40,141
sorry for your troubles.

485
00:23:41,077 --> 00:23:42,377
How bad is it?

486
00:23:43,113 --> 00:23:45,413
I got no crew. I got no cash.

487
00:23:46,149 --> 00:23:47,649
Never been worse.

488
00:23:48,351 --> 00:23:50,051
- Let me ask around.
- [SIGHS]

489
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:53,321
See if any of my guys
have heard who it could be.

490
00:23:54,491 --> 00:23:55,957
I'd appreciate it.

491
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,627
You'll pull through,
Fred. You always do.

492
00:23:59,630 --> 00:24:02,664
But you might wanna keep
tabs on that boy of yours.

493
00:24:09,335 --> 00:24:12,436
NANA ROSE: This necklace
reads the baby's aura.

494
00:24:12,439 --> 00:24:14,489
Predicts the sex.

495
00:24:14,492 --> 00:24:16,778
Nana has dementia and gypsy blood.

496
00:24:18,146 --> 00:24:20,080
- Oh!
- What?

497
00:24:20,083 --> 00:24:21,382
Is my baby okay?

498
00:24:22,219 --> 00:24:23,651
Babies.

499
00:24:24,354 --> 00:24:26,120
It's twins.

500
00:24:26,123 --> 00:24:27,589
One of each!

501
00:24:27,592 --> 00:24:30,859
This is occultism at its most ludicrous.

502
00:24:31,494 --> 00:24:33,361
But I'm grateful to be here.

503
00:24:34,931 --> 00:24:37,365
Oh! Thanks guys!

504
00:24:39,022 --> 00:24:40,188
Okay, now Mom's.

505
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:53,915
It's my nightlight.
When I was a little kid.

506
00:24:53,917 --> 00:24:54,983
[CROWD EXCLAIMS]

507
00:24:54,985 --> 00:24:56,684
How did you... Where did you even...

508
00:24:56,686 --> 00:25:00,244
I saved it. I know how much you loved
it and how it made you feel safe.

509
00:25:00,247 --> 00:25:02,857
And I wanted you to be able to pass
it down to your own baby one day.

510
00:25:02,859 --> 00:25:04,192
Alice, it's lovely.

511
00:25:07,797 --> 00:25:09,364
Open ours next, dear.

512
00:25:17,024 --> 00:25:19,240
You were protecting him.
That's why you didn't tell me.

513
00:25:19,242 --> 00:25:20,308
Relax.

514
00:25:20,310 --> 00:25:21,609
What happened?

515
00:25:22,123 --> 00:25:24,492
Did you know that Jughead's
father is a Serpent?

516
00:25:24,495 --> 00:25:26,107
No.

517
00:25:27,178 --> 00:25:30,218
That's why he tried to stop me from
going to the bar, so I wouldn't find out.

518
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:32,020
After everything my
dad has done for you...

519
00:25:32,022 --> 00:25:34,327
Archie. I can explain, okay?

520
00:25:34,330 --> 00:25:35,630
But not right now.

521
00:25:35,633 --> 00:25:38,459
This is Polly's day, so you
two need to check yourselves.

522
00:25:38,461 --> 00:25:39,661
I mean it.

523
00:25:39,664 --> 00:25:41,329
- Archie...
- No, save it.

524
00:25:42,365 --> 00:25:43,531
Come on.

525
00:25:44,465 --> 00:25:47,299
PENELOPE: That is a family heirloom.

526
00:25:47,302 --> 00:25:52,273
Great-grandfather Blossom used to
play with it. Isn't it magnificent?

527
00:25:52,276 --> 00:25:55,009
Oh, Polly, come stay
with us at Thornhill.

528
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:58,813
Cheryl's invitation is genuine.

529
00:25:59,616 --> 00:26:02,600
Thornhill's gates will
always be open to you.

530
00:26:02,603 --> 00:26:04,686
The child would want for nothing.

531
00:26:04,688 --> 00:26:07,421
You would want for nothing.

532
00:26:07,424 --> 00:26:12,527
Do you think that you can just waltz in
here, with a bedbug-infested Trojan Horse,

533
00:26:12,530 --> 00:26:15,596
wave a blank check around
and steal my daughter?

534
00:26:15,599 --> 00:26:17,665
I didn't think you wanted her,

535
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:21,269
else why would she have
been exiled like some pariah?

536
00:26:21,272 --> 00:26:23,671
To keep her away from your family.

537
00:26:24,341 --> 00:26:25,540
PENELOPE: Oh...

538
00:26:26,260 --> 00:26:28,954
And not because you're ashamed?

539
00:26:28,957 --> 00:26:32,780
Why is your own daughter
not living with you?

540
00:26:32,782 --> 00:26:35,950
She's not going to set
foot in that twisted,

541
00:26:35,952 --> 00:26:37,785
poisonous house of yours.

542
00:26:37,787 --> 00:26:39,220
She should be so lucky.

543
00:26:39,222 --> 00:26:41,249
Cheryl, that's not helping.

544
00:26:41,252 --> 00:26:43,524
She'd do a lot better
there than with you.

545
00:26:43,527 --> 00:26:45,061
How dare you?

546
00:26:45,064 --> 00:26:47,328
Enough! Both of you!

547
00:26:47,331 --> 00:26:48,696
If you believe one lie...

548
00:26:48,698 --> 00:26:50,865
POLLY: This is why Jason is dead!

549
00:26:50,868 --> 00:26:54,936
Because of this hate. This
pointless, stupid fighting.

550
00:26:54,938 --> 00:26:56,537
- Honey...
- No, don't touch me.

551
00:26:56,540 --> 00:26:58,520
We were supposed to be together.

552
00:26:59,832 --> 00:27:02,285
And you didn't let us
have that, neither of you.

553
00:27:03,346 --> 00:27:05,446
And you know it cost Jason his life.

554
00:27:05,449 --> 00:27:07,415
Polly.

555
00:27:20,094 --> 00:27:21,861
Mom.

556
00:27:21,864 --> 00:27:24,463
You need to talk to her.

557
00:27:33,119 --> 00:27:35,307
Polly, I'm sorry.

558
00:27:35,310 --> 00:27:38,190
- It's just that woman...
- Didn't send me away.

559
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:40,613
You did.

560
00:27:43,951 --> 00:27:46,585
And if you hadn't, I
would've met up with Jason,

561
00:27:46,588 --> 00:27:48,308
and he still might be alive.

562
00:27:49,107 --> 00:27:52,585
Or you might've gotten hurt or worse.

563
00:27:52,588 --> 00:27:55,060
I was alone there.

564
00:27:55,063 --> 00:27:57,028
In that place.

565
00:27:57,031 --> 00:28:01,267
I never wanted you to
feel alone, or unwanted,

566
00:28:01,270 --> 00:28:03,402
or unloved.

567
00:28:05,918 --> 00:28:08,374
Honey, come home.

568
00:28:08,377 --> 00:28:11,310
I promise you you'll
never feel that way again.

569
00:28:13,714 --> 00:28:15,047
You want me to come home?

570
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:17,833
More than anything, honey.

571
00:28:17,836 --> 00:28:19,585
Yeah, but what about Dad?

572
00:28:20,221 --> 00:28:21,320
Your father...

573
00:28:21,322 --> 00:28:23,722
Dad's just gonna have to get over it.

574
00:28:23,725 --> 00:28:27,700
Are you sure he's not just gonna try
and make another appointment for me?

575
00:28:27,703 --> 00:28:29,602
What are you talking
about? What appointment?

576
00:28:30,849 --> 00:28:34,800
Before you sent me away, Dad made an
appointment for me to see a doctor.

577
00:28:34,803 --> 00:28:37,970
Said he would be more
than happy to pay for it.

578
00:28:39,072 --> 00:28:41,539
That I shouldn't have
to live with my mistake.

579
00:28:41,542 --> 00:28:43,475
Oh, my God...

580
00:28:43,478 --> 00:28:46,278
He didn't even ask me what I wanted.

581
00:29:05,622 --> 00:29:07,933
Dad, before you say anything,
I was trying to help.

582
00:29:07,935 --> 00:29:09,911
- It was reckless.
- Yeah, but it doesn't matter.

583
00:29:09,914 --> 00:29:11,909
I wanna pull my weight around here.

584
00:29:11,912 --> 00:29:14,081
I wanna help you the way you help me.

585
00:29:14,084 --> 00:29:16,336
We've both done everything we can.

586
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:21,080
I need you to know, son...

587
00:29:22,651 --> 00:29:26,285
I tried, my whole life, to build stuff.

588
00:29:26,287 --> 00:29:29,321
I tried to build a family,
that didn't work out.

589
00:29:29,323 --> 00:29:33,993
I'm trying to build
us a safe life for you.

590
00:29:33,996 --> 00:29:37,296
And the jury's still out on that.

591
00:29:40,148 --> 00:29:43,068
I've been pouring
concrete and laying brick

592
00:29:43,070 --> 00:29:44,903
since I was your age.

593
00:29:47,675 --> 00:29:49,241
That's who I am.

594
00:29:51,245 --> 00:29:52,778
It's all I am.

595
00:29:56,017 --> 00:29:58,050
Dad, I was thinking,

596
00:30:02,556 --> 00:30:05,659
what if I have a kid someday,

597
00:30:05,662 --> 00:30:08,120
and what if that kid hates music,

598
00:30:08,123 --> 00:30:09,902
doesn't want anything to do with it,

599
00:30:10,690 --> 00:30:12,431
and says, instead... [EXHALES]

600
00:30:13,501 --> 00:30:16,547
"Nah, I wanna build houses
and buildings like Grandpa."

601
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:19,738
I think that would be
pretty friggin' cool, Dad.

602
00:30:21,188 --> 00:30:23,088
That would be something.

603
00:30:25,980 --> 00:30:31,050
This is your legacy,
which makes it mine, too.

604
00:30:43,631 --> 00:30:45,464
Polly's finally asleep.

605
00:30:47,701 --> 00:30:49,368
What a mess.

606
00:30:53,407 --> 00:30:55,908
I should've told you about
my dad when I had the chance.

607
00:30:58,179 --> 00:30:59,778
So, why didn't you?

608
00:31:00,414 --> 00:31:02,247
I was ashamed.

609
00:31:03,806 --> 00:31:05,239
Jughead,

610
00:31:06,454 --> 00:31:08,153
if we're gonna be together,

611
00:31:08,156 --> 00:31:11,023
I want to know who you are.

612
00:31:11,026 --> 00:31:13,025
All of it.

613
00:31:14,128 --> 00:31:15,661
Okay.

614
00:31:17,231 --> 00:31:18,530
Okay.

615
00:31:20,201 --> 00:31:22,801
But Juggy, we should talk to your dad.

616
00:31:24,305 --> 00:31:27,606
He might know something about Jason.

617
00:31:39,887 --> 00:31:41,053
Jughead!

618
00:31:41,056 --> 00:31:43,222
Dad, Betty Cooper.

619
00:31:43,225 --> 00:31:44,957
Betty, this is my dad.

620
00:31:44,959 --> 00:31:47,259
Hi, Mr. Jones, nice to
meet you, officially.

621
00:31:47,261 --> 00:31:48,861
And you, and you. Um...

622
00:31:48,864 --> 00:31:52,006
Why don't you guys sit down?

623
00:31:52,016 --> 00:31:55,560
This isn't really a social call.

624
00:31:55,571 --> 00:31:58,939
No. I didn't expect it would be
after Archie showed up at the bar.

625
00:31:58,942 --> 00:32:01,308
We know the Serpents had
some kind of drug thing

626
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:03,010
going on with Jason Blossom.

627
00:32:03,013 --> 00:32:04,578
What?

628
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:06,509
Where'd you hear that?

629
00:32:06,512 --> 00:32:08,615
- Jason's girlfriend.
- My sister.

630
00:32:10,919 --> 00:32:12,085
[SIGHS]

631
00:32:17,630 --> 00:32:20,731
The kid needed some money to get away.

632
00:32:22,067 --> 00:32:24,698
A clean-cut kid like that, no
one's gonna suspect him of running,

633
00:32:24,700 --> 00:32:27,067
so we helped him, he helped us.

634
00:32:27,069 --> 00:32:29,036
Jeez, Dad. Did you tell the cops that?

635
00:32:29,038 --> 00:32:30,670
What do you think?

636
00:32:31,607 --> 00:32:34,241
Well, they know now. Polly told them.

637
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,970
So if they haven't been
by yet, they will be.

638
00:32:37,646 --> 00:32:40,280
Did you ever talk to Jason? Personally?

639
00:32:40,282 --> 00:32:42,049
My guys gave him some product.

640
00:32:42,051 --> 00:32:46,620
When it wasn't delivered, we figured
he'd took off with our stash, until...

641
00:32:46,622 --> 00:32:49,122
Until Jason's body was
found at Sweetwater River.

642
00:32:56,432 --> 00:32:58,432
Anything else you wanna ask?

643
00:33:00,832 --> 00:33:03,766
Did you have anything to do
with Jason Blossom's death?

644
00:33:07,042 --> 00:33:08,875
You really think I could do that?

645
00:33:08,878 --> 00:33:11,278
It's the dark ages, Dad.

646
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,780
I don't really know
what to think anymore.

647
00:33:15,517 --> 00:33:17,984
I'm not a perfect father,
Jughead, no getting around that,

648
00:33:17,986 --> 00:33:21,955
but... I'm no killer.

649
00:33:30,599 --> 00:33:31,898
[DOG BARKING]

650
00:33:35,618 --> 00:33:38,839
- Do you believe him?
- I do.

651
00:33:41,919 --> 00:33:43,085
Do you?

652
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:47,133
I believe you, Jughead.

653
00:34:05,968 --> 00:34:08,201
[SPORTS ANNOUNCERS CHATTERING]

654
00:34:14,235 --> 00:34:15,213
Honey?

655
00:34:15,216 --> 00:34:18,578
What did you say to Polly when you
found out that she was pregnant?

656
00:34:18,580 --> 00:34:20,580
Did you make an appointment for her?

657
00:34:21,550 --> 00:34:23,250
With a doctor?

658
00:34:23,253 --> 00:34:26,152
That you offered to pay for?

659
00:34:26,155 --> 00:34:27,921
Behind my back?

660
00:34:28,925 --> 00:34:32,685
So that she could fix
her... Her mistake?

661
00:34:34,897 --> 00:34:36,129
Alice.

662
00:34:36,131 --> 00:34:37,797
Bastard!

663
00:34:42,706 --> 00:34:47,474
So you did to Polly
exactly what you did to me?

664
00:34:48,417 --> 00:34:53,113
See, this is why I didn't
involve you, for this very reason.

665
00:34:53,115 --> 00:34:54,981
I knew that you would overreact.

666
00:34:56,118 --> 00:34:59,486
Honey, you weren't ready, okay?

667
00:34:59,488 --> 00:35:00,921
And neither is Polly.

668
00:35:00,924 --> 00:35:03,623
We were sending her to the Sisters.

669
00:35:04,193 --> 00:35:05,859
Why wasn't that enough?

670
00:35:05,862 --> 00:35:09,162
Because of exactly what
is happening right now.

671
00:35:09,998 --> 00:35:13,099
Our little girl's life is being ruined

672
00:35:13,558 --> 00:35:15,224
by that mistake.

673
00:35:15,227 --> 00:35:18,756
By that family.

674
00:35:18,759 --> 00:35:22,742
Polly is moving home, into
this house, where she belongs.

675
00:35:22,744 --> 00:35:24,311
The hell she is, Alice!

676
00:35:26,114 --> 00:35:28,014
'Cause I will not be party

677
00:35:28,016 --> 00:35:29,482
to raising a child

678
00:35:29,484 --> 00:35:32,052
that has Blossom blood.

679
00:35:34,323 --> 00:35:35,488
Get out.

680
00:35:35,491 --> 00:35:36,723
No.

681
00:35:39,795 --> 00:35:42,596
Get out!

682
00:35:42,598 --> 00:35:43,897
Get out!

683
00:35:43,899 --> 00:35:47,367
Get out before I do
something that we both regret.

684
00:35:48,770 --> 00:35:52,439
And I think, by now, you
know what I'm capable of.

685
00:35:52,442 --> 00:35:55,460
No. What would people think?

686
00:35:58,333 --> 00:36:01,268
I don't... I don't care anymore.

687
00:36:01,271 --> 00:36:03,883
And I am not gonna ask again.

688
00:36:05,187 --> 00:36:06,586
Get out.

689
00:36:08,594 --> 00:36:11,637
I don't want you here
when Polly gets home.

690
00:36:27,445 --> 00:36:30,570
[ARCHIE PRACTICING GUITAR]

691
00:36:45,339 --> 00:36:46,739
I should've trusted you.

692
00:36:46,742 --> 00:36:49,241
There's no excuse.

693
00:36:50,211 --> 00:36:53,379
I was afraid that the
Serpents and my dad

694
00:36:53,381 --> 00:36:55,247
were the ones doing
those messed up things.

695
00:36:56,717 --> 00:36:58,684
I didn't wanna believe that was true.

696
00:37:00,354 --> 00:37:03,922
I mean... [SIGHS] He's my dad, Archie.

697
00:37:04,625 --> 00:37:07,259
I get that. I do.

698
00:37:08,963 --> 00:37:11,664
But, Jughead, you can
talk to me about anything.

699
00:37:12,133 --> 00:37:13,565
You're like...

700
00:37:16,504 --> 00:37:18,137
[QUIETLY] You're like my brother.

701
00:37:20,207 --> 00:37:21,974
Nice bro-whisper, Archie.

702
00:37:24,111 --> 00:37:25,311
You are my brother.

703
00:37:26,681 --> 00:37:28,647
And I'm here for you and your dad.

704
00:37:28,649 --> 00:37:29,815
So what can I do?

705
00:37:31,252 --> 00:37:33,152
Pray for a miracle.

706
00:37:37,992 --> 00:37:40,793
The heat is on. If
the cops come around...

707
00:37:43,130 --> 00:37:44,730
This is our insurance.

708
00:37:44,733 --> 00:37:46,697
In case everything goes to hell.

709
00:37:46,700 --> 00:37:50,402
Here, stash it. Keep it safe.

710
00:37:53,407 --> 00:37:55,074
How's it going with the Keller kid?

711
00:37:55,077 --> 00:37:57,376
It's good. He thinks we're legit.

712
00:37:57,379 --> 00:37:58,612
Right on.

713
00:37:58,615 --> 00:38:01,146
We're gonna need that
inside line with the Sheriff.

714
00:38:04,817 --> 00:38:06,117
What?

715
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,519
We got a problem?

716
00:38:08,723 --> 00:38:10,622
He likes me, you know... For real.

717
00:38:12,993 --> 00:38:15,126
[SCOFFS]

718
00:38:15,129 --> 00:38:17,329
[CHUCKLING]

719
00:38:17,331 --> 00:38:18,964
Ah, you're breaking my heart.

720
00:38:20,699 --> 00:38:22,633
We all got a part to play.

721
00:38:22,636 --> 00:38:24,536
Including me.

722
00:38:31,105 --> 00:38:33,445
I've got calls into
Greendale and Centerville.

723
00:38:33,448 --> 00:38:36,148
Clifford Blossom couldn't have
hired every crew in the state.

724
00:38:36,150 --> 00:38:39,318
In the meantime, we'll
just be a two-person crew.

725
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,019
FP: That won't be necessary.

726
00:38:42,289 --> 00:38:43,555
You need a crew?

727
00:38:43,558 --> 00:38:45,924
My guys are always looking for work.

728
00:38:47,094 --> 00:38:49,495
And you've never had a
better foreman than me.

729
00:38:52,233 --> 00:38:54,466
I won't leave you hanging this time.

730
00:38:55,669 --> 00:38:57,002
What if there's trouble?

731
00:38:58,539 --> 00:39:01,173
We can handle trouble.

732
00:39:04,211 --> 00:39:05,811
We're burning daylight.

733
00:39:06,471 --> 00:39:07,770
Let's get going.

734
00:39:07,773 --> 00:39:10,307
I'll catch up. We're just
gonna get the paperwork done.

735
00:39:13,888 --> 00:39:17,589
I asked around about those bruisers
going after your man's crew.

736
00:39:17,592 --> 00:39:19,491
Turns out they weren't local.

737
00:39:20,635 --> 00:39:22,668
Why are you telling me, not Fred?

738
00:39:22,671 --> 00:39:26,298
One of my guys says he knows 'em
from a stint doing time up north,

739
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:27,866
in Montreal.

740
00:39:30,471 --> 00:39:33,272
Pretty sure we both know
who has business in Montreal.

741
00:39:33,741 --> 00:39:35,841
Hiram? But...

742
00:39:35,844 --> 00:39:37,609
Why would he...

743
00:39:37,611 --> 00:39:40,131
Maybe he got a whiff of your
little romance with Freddy Andrews?

744
00:39:41,182 --> 00:39:44,483
But the real question
is, who ratted you out?

745
00:39:49,990 --> 00:39:52,057
Mom had no idea, Polly.

746
00:39:52,793 --> 00:39:55,027
Dad never told her. She swears it.

747
00:39:56,397 --> 00:39:58,096
[SIGHS] I just...

748
00:39:58,098 --> 00:39:59,798
I can't believe she kicked him out.

749
00:39:59,801 --> 00:40:01,567
She meant what she said.

750
00:40:01,570 --> 00:40:08,172
She wants you and the baby,
or babies, to feel safe.

751
00:40:08,175 --> 00:40:09,908
Which means...

752
00:40:11,245 --> 00:40:12,744
You can come home now.

753
